00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:17,320
hard to make a universal flu vaccine. The coronaviruses in general tend to be much more

195
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:21,000
stable, even though there's some diversity among them, and we might have cross protection, which

196
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:25,000
would be useful to take other threats like Middle East respiratory syndrome and the original SARS

197
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:31,720
off the table as well. When H1N1 hit, you sort of alluded to this briefly, the case fatality rate

